PhD in Cinema by Sorbonne, France, and post-doctoral by the Université du Quebéc à Montreal, Rosa Berardo has come a long way in Audiovisual, participating as a director and as a juri in many film festivals in Brasil and internationally, as in Locarno, Clermont Ferrant, Asolo, Portugal and Goiás. In the photographic area, she made a series of national and international exhibits and her name can be found at the Virtual Woman Library as one of the brazillian artists that stood out the most in the arts field over the last years.

"I believe on the production and thriving of brazillian movies. More than that... I believe in the movie’s strenght and in those who want to invest and improve their knowledge about cinema and it’s practice."

Rosa Berardo

Doctorate in Cinema by Sorbonne, France, and post-doctorate by Université du Québec à Montreal. Moviemaker, Journalist, Photographer and Teacher.

In 2002, Rosa funded the first Cinema School on Goiás State, called SKÓPOS. In 2010, Rosa created the House of Cinema (Maison du Cinema) as a moviemaking studio, where students could learn and fulfill their dreams on learning about cinema in Goiás. The House already graduated more than 80 new movie makers and vídeo productors in Goiás. Seven (07) short films have already been made by the school students and many productions in Goiânia bear the signature and sponsorship of her school. Many of these movies received prizes in national and local festivals, like Goiânia Mostra Curtas, and also have been exhibited on FICA (International Ambiental Cinema Festival).

About

Doctorate in Cinema by Sorbonne, France, and post-doctorate by Université du Québec à Montreal. Moviemaker, Journalist, Photographer and Teacher. In 2002, Rosa funded the first Cinema School on Goiás State, called SKÓPOS. In 2010, Rosa created the House of Cinema (Maison du Cinema) as a moviemaking studio, where students could learn and fulfill their dreams on learning about cinema in Goiás. The House already graduated more than 80 new movie makers and vídeo productors in Goiás. Seven (07) short films have already been made by the school students and many productions in Goiânia bear the signature and sponsorship of her school. Many of these movies received prizes in national and local festivals, like Goiânia Mostra Curtas, and also have been exhibited on FICA (International Ambiental Cinema Festival). PhD in Cinema by Sorbonne, France, and post-doctoral by the Université du Quebéc à Montreal, Rosa Berardo has come a long way in Audiovisual, participating as a director and as a juri in many film festivals in Brasil and internationally, as in Locarno, Clermont Ferrant, Asolo, Portugal and Goiás. In the photographic area, she made a series of national and international exhibits and her name can be found at the Virtual Woman Library (www.bibliotecavirtualdamulher.com.br) as one of the brazillian artists that stood out the most in the arts field over the last years. In 2002, Rosa Berardo created the First Cinema School of the State of Goiás, SKÔPOS. During two years, she coordinated the postgraduate course in Cinema and in 2005, she transferred the course to Cambury College, where she continued as coordinator of another group of graduate students. She left coordination in June 2005 to pursue post-doctoral training in Canada. In July 2007, she was honored with the highest award of the State of Goiás in the culture area: Comenda Anhanguera, delivered by the Governor of the State Alcides Rodrigues, in the city of Goiás. Currently, Rosa Berardo teaches at the University of Goiás (FAV-UFG) at the Faculty of Visual Arts of the Federal University of Goiás. She produces films and teaches courses at the Casa do Cinema, and she has been invited to teach film courses in renowned universities abroad: Université du Québec à Montréal, Canada; Université de Bordeaux 3- France, Ohio University- USA, University of Sinaloa- Mexico, University of Ouarzazate - Morocco, National University of Jujuy - Salta and University of Montreal. item.title: Romaria do Vão do Moleque
item.dc:creator: editor
item.content:encoded:
Documentário realizado junto ao grupo étnico Kalunga na região de Cavalcante.

Durante 8 dias sua equipe ficou no local onde aconteceu a Romaria gravando entrevistas

e imagens dos participantes bem como de todas as etapas de preparação

e realização das manifestações tradicionais de cultura.

item.title: Meninos Verdes
item.dc:creator: editor
item.content:encoded:
Curta metragem em animação adaptado da obra homônima
da escritora Cora Coralina, de cunho ambiental.
O filme fala sobre pequenas criaturas verdes
que aparecem no quintal da escritora.

item.title: A Chegada de Aninha
item.dc:creator: editor
item.content:encoded:
Curta metragem de animação sobre a infância de Cora Coralina.

É inspirado em seu livro Vintém de Cobre e narra detalhes

das dificuldades econômicas e também da rejeição familiar

a que a escritora foi submetida durante sua infância

item.title: A Chegada de Aninha
item.dc:creator: editor
item.content:encoded:
A Chegada de Aninha (The Arrival of Aninha)

Short animation film about the childhood of Cora Coralina.

It is inspired by her book Vintém de Cobre, the theme revolves around economic difficulties and the family rejection to which the writer was subjected during her childhood.
